Treaty of Panavia

* Panavia will become a close partner of the USK, meaning that it will get complete security guarantees, economic investments, dollarization of the economy, technological support, weapons supply, resource supply, amongst other things.

* In exchange, people between Kameri and Panavia will have both free access to both countries without a passport and the border will be completely open for both.

* In exchange, military bases will be built in the straits between the islands, to attain control over the maritime trade routes and begin charging taxes to every ship that crossed the strait.

* In exchange, Panavia shall give military access to the USK and access to air bases for operations in south Karemi.

Pact of Steel Treaty:

The president gives the emperor a piece of paper detailing the next:

Article 1: The Pact of Steels is a declaration of free states around the world who are likeminded and want to work for a more just, free world. Due to the aggressive actions of certain nations that hold great power.

Article 2: The Pact of Steel would attempt to include: Quokka, The Jovian Shogunate, Senshi and Panavia with the United States at the helm to organize a harmonious and properly functional coalition.

Article 3: The Pact would allow for free commerce around all members with no restrictions, and would give priority of supply to member nations for greater profits and more benefits for the strengthening of our nations.

Article 4: In offensive operations, a summit would be called to see what aid every nation is willing to lend to the nation that is executing the offensive operation, but it won’t be obligatory.

Article 5: An attack on one member would be an attack on all members, this is only for purely defensive wars, but it will give an umbrella of deterrence to all member nations.

Article 6: Intelligence agencies in all member nations must collaborate with each other to root out foreign agents and cells in member countries.

Article 7: Member countries will enjoy the latest and most powerful weapons with them receiving the original versions instead of inferior export versions given to non-members in case of purchase.

Article 8: All members would be able to use the dollar or gold for payments between each other for ease of currency, but they would keep their national currency to not overstep their sovereignty.

Article 9: Should a member state fall, we will receive their leaders with open arms in asylum/exile.

## Treaty of Kih Lao

The Kingdom of Kih Lao proposes a peace treaty to end hostilities in the region.

Kih Lao shall be partitioned into three regions - with one region remaining partially independent, as a protectorate to the Maurian Empire; Western Kih Lao shall be administered by the Maurian Empire; and Eastern Kih Lao shall be annexed by the Republic of Indosia.

Indosia will also need to pay reparations to the victims of the unification war with Kih Lao.

Signed this 24th day of July, 1903.

Treaty of Maripol

I. The state of Javashi and its armed forces will surrender to the Realm of Xeralasha Lakesh. The government will apologize for all actions it has committed before being completely disbanded.

II. The land of Javashi will be annexed by the Realm of Xeralasha Lakesh and will now be under the law of Lakesh.

III. All equipment of the armed forces of Javashi will be transferred to the military of Lakesh.

IV. All gold reserves will be transferred to Lakesh.

V. The people of Javashi will be treated the same as that of Lakesh.

VI. A garrison of five infantry and two order divisions will be established in the region to maintain order. They are to act as the administration until the government is able to properly take over.

VII. All foreign assets within the region will be seized and if possible nationalized.

6shindeiru05/04/24
Non-Aggression Pact

This Non-Aggression Pact is entered into between @pico0049 and @6shindeiru on 4th January 1964, with the intention of promoting peace, stability, and mutual respect between the parties.

1. Non-Aggression:
a. Both parties agree not to engage in any form of aggression, including but not limited to military aggression and economic coercion.
b. Neither party shall support, directly or indirectly, any hostile actions against the other party by third parties.

2. Conflict Resolution:
In the event of any disputes or disagreements arising between the parties, both parties commit to resolving them through peaceful means, such as negotiation, mediation, or arbitration.

3. Respect for Sovereignty:
Both parties affirm their respect for each other's sovereignty, territorial integrity, and political independence. They shall refrain from any actions that may undermine or challenge these principles.

4. Communication and Cooperation:
Both parties agree to maintain open channels of communication and foster cooperation in areas of mutual interest, such as trade, cultural exchange, and scientific collaboration, to enhance trust and understanding between them.

5. Duration and Termination:
This Pact shall remain in force indefinitely, unless terminated by mutual agreement of the parties. Either party may terminate this Pact by providing written notice to the other party [specify notice period].

6. Amendment:
Any amendments or modifications to this Pact shall be made in writing and require the consent of both parties.

7. Final Provisions:
a. This Pact constitutes the entire agreement between the parties concerning its subject matter and supersedes all prior agreements and understandings, whether oral or written.
b. Any disputes arising out of or in connection with this Pact shall be resolved through negotiations between the parties.
